<br>
&quot;Why don't we use epic pet, rather than fire pet?&quot;<br>
<br>
Well, not every mage has their epic pet.  It takes a lot of resources to finish the mage epic, more than any other epic as far as I can see, and most mages don't have access to the epic pet.<br>
<br>
&quot;Does the fire pet have low hp's?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, the lowest of all pets out there -- slightly more than half of what an earth pet has.  The 1-49 fire pets at least had an amazing DS that allowed them to do a lot of damage.<br>
<br>
&quot;Do mages tank for their pets?&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, absolutely.  All the time, actually.  If you have decent gear, it's rather easy to tank for your fire pet :-)  Most lvl 60 mages that have focused on HP's have more than the fire pet.  Those of us who are lower level do it so that the pet has some uninterrupted bashing time.<br>
<br>
Plus, it impresses the newbies.<br>
<br>
&quot;What level is the fire pet's DS?&quot;<br>
<br>
Pre-50, it's level of the pet + 2.  This is different than level of the summon spell + 2.  At 49, our best fire pet is 41st level, which would make its DS 43.<br>
<br>
Post-50, it casts your 5pt damage shield.  Now this does stack with our DS's, but doesn't make much difference, since this pet doesn't get agro very easily.<br>
<br>
&quot;Does the fire pet hit the same as other pets?&quot;<br>
<br>
Nope, best hit the 52 fire pet does is 29, which is half of what a 51 elemental does (5<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  The 58 pet does slightly better than half damage of the 57 earth.<br>
<br>
&quot;Why use the post-50 fire pet at all?&quot;<br>
<br>
Most of us don't.  Occasionally, you'll get one that chain stuns, and if that's the case, you'll have a pet that is better than the next level air pet at stunning the mob.  At least, as long as it's mana lasts.<br>
<br>
Otherwise, it's a waste of malachite.<br>
<br>
That's actually the point of the original poster.  We mages want to have our pets be useful and most of us can't see the utility of the post-50 fire pets.<br>
<br>
Now, I'm not sure that giving the pet lure spells is reasonable, either.  Mostly because I don't think it would make enough of a difference to actually make me want to use the pet.<br>
<br>
But I at least wanted to clear up the misinformation.<br>
<br>
--<br>
Eloina Pyromancer<br>
52nd Elementalist<br>
